'''Sandy Rothman''' (born 30 January 1946, [[Miami, Florida]]<ref>[http://bluegrasstoday.com/blog/2011/01/30/i%E2%80%99m-going-back-to-old-kentucky-122/ ''Bluegrass Today'', 30 January 2011]</ref>) is a [[San Francisco Bay Area]] [[Bluegrass music|bluegrass]] [[multi-instrumentalist]] and record producer, who plays [[mandolin]], [[dobro]] and [[banjo]], and was a friend and colleague of [[Grateful Dead]] bandleader [[Jerry Garcia]], and a member of the [[Jerry Garcia Acoustic Band]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Chadbourne |first=Eugene |url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/sandy-rothman-p120543/biography |title=Sandy Rothman |publisher=AllMusic |date= |accessdate=2011-10-24}}</ref> He played bluegrass with Garcia and [[David Nelson (musician)|David Nelson]] as the Black Mountain Boys in 1964,<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=w3y3PbFPNe4C&pg=PA61&dq=%22sandy+rothman%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=pkZ5T7i_CeWTiQKWi42pDg&ved=0CFoQ6AEwBg#v=onepage&q=%22sandy%20rothman%22&f=false ''Garcia: An American Life'', Blair Jackson (p. 61)]</ref> and has played with [[Bill Monroe]] and his Blue Grass Boys,<ref>[http://books.google.com/books?id=GAbnm5EdCu0C&pg=PA81&dq=%22sandy+rothman%22&hl=en&sa=X&ei=pkZ5T7i_CeWTiQKWi42pDg&ved=0CGYQ6AEwCA#v=onepage&q=%22sandy%20rothman%22&f=false ''Bean Blossom: The Brown County Jamboree and Bill Monroe's Bluegrass Festivals'', Thomas A. Adler (p. 81)]</ref> [[Foggy Mountain Boys#Members|Earl Taylor]], [[Red Allen]], [[Jimmie Skinner]], [[Larry Sparks]], the [[Kentucky Colonels (band)|Kentucky Colonels]], [[Country Joe McDonald]],<ref>[http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=SBkhAAAAIBAJ&sjid=m0cEAAAAIBAJ&pg=5077,5119813&dq=sandy-rothman&hl=en "Country Joe' Mcdonald Tries Singing A New Tune", ''Daily News'' (Bowling Green, Kentucky) June 21, 1991]</ref> [[Kathy Kallick]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allmusic.com/artist/sandy-rothman-p120543/credits |title=Sandy Rothman |publisher=AllMusic |date= |accessdate=2011-10-24}}</ref> and [[Clarence White]], among other musicians. He has been described as "one of the chief [[Beaten biscuit|biscuits]] when and where bluegrass music is discussed, scribed, or performed in northern California."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.well.com/user/smarcus/sr/Sandy.html |title=Sandy Rothman's Home Page |publisher=Well.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-24}}</ref>

==Discography==
*''[[Almost Acoustic]]'', [[Jerry Garcia Acoustic Band]], [[Arista Records]] (1988) (producer and performer)
*''Bluegrass Guitar Duets'', with Steve Pottier, [[Sierra Records]] (1994)
*''[[Pure Jerry: Lunt-Fontanne, New York City, October 31, 1987]]'' <U+2013> [[Jerry Garcia Band]] and Jerry Garcia Acoustic Band (2004)
*''[[Pure Jerry: Lunt-Fontanne, New York City, The Best of the Rest, October 15<U+2013>30, 1987]]'' <U+2013> Jerry Garcia Band and Jerry Garcia Acoustic Band (2004) 
*''[[Jesse McReynolds]] & Friends: Songs of the Grateful Dead: A Tribute to Jerry Garcia and Robert Hunter'', [[Woodstock Records]] (2010) producer and performer)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jimandjesse.com/resources/TributetoJerryGarciaandRobertHunter.php |title=w w w . j i m a n d j e s s e . c o m |publisher=Jimandjesse.com |date= |accessdate=2011-10-24}}</ref><ref>[http://in.reuters.com/article/2010/10/27/idINIndia-52470520101027 "Bluegrass legend (Jesse McReynolds) puts out album of Grateful Dead music", Randall Mikkelsen, Reuters, October 27, 2010]</ref><ref>[http://www.nashvillescene.com/nashville/songs-of-the-grateful-dead-feat-jesse-mcreynolds-and-more/Event?oid=2593461 Review, ''Nashville Scene'', August 4, 2011]</ref>
*''[[Ragged but Right]]'', Jerry Garcia Acoustic Band, [[Rhino Records]] (2010) (recorded in 1987) (producer and performer)

